Five Thousand Dead, at Least Five Thousand Missing in Honduras

Tegucigalpa 11-3 (AFP) - The Honduran Transportation Minister, Thomas Lucano, confirmed today, Tuesday, in Tegucigalpa that the floods and mudslides resulting from Hurricane Mitch inflicted five thousand fatalities and resulted in at least five thousands missing in Honduras.
  
During a visit to the devastated areas in the capital, the Minister added that 70 percent of the road network has been destroyed in addition to 164 bridges.
 
The Honduran President, Carlos Flores, confirmed to reporters that 900 thousand people, or one sixth of the country's population, have been evacuated or were directly harmed by the hurricane.  
